{#-
name: network-service-hardening
summary: Network listeners need IP filtering (Tailscale CGNAT + localhost) and auth; no unauthenticated endpoints.
domain: engineering
audience: agent
severity: default
tags: [network, security, tailscale, auth, hardening]
scope: [any]
phase: [planning, executing, reviewing]
-#}
Any code that listens on a network port must have both:

1. **IP filtering** — Tailscale CGNAT (`100.64.0.0/10`) and localhost only. Reject everything else.
2. **Authentication** — bearer token, shared secret, or equivalent. No unauthenticated endpoints.

Binding to `0.0.0.0` is fine when filtering happens in the request handler (more robust than interface binding when Tailscale connects after server start). Return terse 401/403 errors with no details.
